    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "committed_2016_high_econ",
    "description": "Maps the committed_split threshold in the 2016-block retarget regime at high economic support (econ=0.78). Companion to targeted_sweep1_committed_threshold (144-block) and targeted_sweep6_pool_ideology_full.\nRESEARCH QUESTION: In the 144-block regime, v27 loses when committed_split \u2272 0.214 (v27 gets only ~15% of committed hashrate). Does this threshold shift in the 2016-block regime, where v27 must accumulate 2016 blocks to trigger the retarget cascade?\nMECHANISM IN 2016-BLOCK REGIME: - Committed v27 pools mine v27 from t=0; neutral pools (30%) drift based on price - v27 must reach 2016 blocks BEFORE v26 retargets (v26 retargets at t\u22488100s based on sweep9) - If committed_split is too low, v27 lacks hashrate to accumulate 2016 blocks in time - Once v27 retargets, committed v26 pool losses jump from ~9% \u2192 ~56%, far above 13.26%\n  tolerance \u2192 cascade completes ~4000s post-retarget\n\nPRIOR CONTEXT: - At committed_split=0.35 (standard), v27 gets 24.5% of hashrate \u2192 wins (sweep10b+) - At committed_split=0.214 (144-block threshold), v27 gets ~15% committed hashrate - econ=0.78 ensures 1 economic node on v27 (confirmed via econ_switching_144_verify) - Cascade timing at econ=0.78 (1 node): baseline t\u22488426s; sigmoid t\u22484239s\nCOMMITTED_SPLIT INTERPRETATION:\n  v27_pct = (1 - neutral_pct/100) * committed_split = 0.70 * committed_split\n  committed_split=0.20: v27=14%, v26=56%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.30: v27=21%, v26=49%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.40: v27=28%, v26=42%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.50: v27=35%, v26=35%, neutral=30%  (symmetric)\n\nEXPECTED OUTCOMES: - committed_split=0.50 (symmetric): v27 should win \u2014 same as our standard sweeps - committed_split=0.30 (~144-block threshold): near the transition \u2014 may go either way - committed_split=0.20: v27 has only 14% committed \u2014 likely v26_dominant - Threshold expected somewhere in [0.20, 0.40]\nRun command:\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input tools/sweep/committed_2016_high_econ/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-com2016-hi \\\n    --results-dir committed_2016_high_econ/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-com2016-hi\n\nWall-clock: 4 scenarios \u00d7 13,000s = 52,000s \u2248 14.4h\n",
